        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We set two Basebands on 12CO 345 GHz line, which is the main target of this Science Goal.
One Baseband is set to cover full absorption feature (far-wings of the absorption line extend in ~several hundred MHz width) of CO with 1.8 GHz bandwidth. As we will measure the far-wing of CO absoption line, we do not need suh a high spatial resolution for this Baseband (2 MHz is sufficient). 
On the other hand, we need a high (~244 kHz) resolution to measure the narrow absorption core of CO line. 
The width of the absorption core is ~10 MHz, and thus we set  234 MHz-width configuration. 

The other two Basebands are set around 335 GHz to measure the HDO and H2O2, which are the same transitions targeted in the another Science Goal of this proposal. 
For HDO and H2O2, we require a higher spectral resolution (~488 kHz and 242 kHz for HDO and H2O2 respectively). Although HDO and H2O2 lines themselves could be as narrow as ~10 MHz (largely depending on how much HDO or H2O2 exists) we set 937 and 240 MHz-bandwidth in order to constain well the continuum level of both lines. 
 </prj:justificationText>
